modules.description: This module computes differences between XML trees and generates patches to transform one tree into another, using a specialized algorithm for handling semi-structured data. It works with XML trees, node labels, paths within the tree, and patch operations such as insertions, deletions, updates, and moves. The core functionality supports synchronizing XML-based document versions, tracking changes in configuration files, and generating human-readable patch logs. Submodules extend this capability with utilities for path resolution, node manipulation, and patch application, enabling precise transformations and detailed change analysis.
